Description: honest infeasibility-reporting I/O moment collector
 iomoments collects per-window method-of-moments statistics (mean,
 variance, skewness, kurtosis) from BPF tracepoints on the block I/O
 path and refuses workloads where the inputs would mislead, instead of
 producing wrong-but-confident output.
 .
 A twelve-signal verdict layer (Carleman ratio, Hill alpha, Jarque-Bera,
 sample-rate adequacy, and others) gates each output window. When a
 signal trips, iomoments reports the failure mode rather than emitting
 numbers that the underlying distribution does not support.
 .
 Beta-trial quality. Requires Linux >= 5.15 with BPF, BTF, and ring-buffer
 support (CONFIG_BPF, CONFIG_BPF_SYSCALL, CONFIG_DEBUG_INFO_BTF).
